# ✍️ Section 7: Task 2 Opinion Essay Introduction

## Welcome to IELTS Writing Task 2

Task 2 is a **250-word essay** written in **40 minutes**.

It is extremely important because it carries a large portion of the Writing score.

---

## 5 Types of Task 2 Essays

| Essay Type | Focus |
|---|---|
| Opinion Essay | Do you agree or disagree? |
| Discussion Essay | Discuss both views |
| Advantages / Disadvantages | Benefits and drawbacks |
| Problem / Solution | Causes and solutions |
| Two-Part Question | Answer two questions |

---

# 🧱 Opinion Essay Structure

## Introduction

**Length:** 50 words

Include:

- General statement
- Paraphrase the question
- Clear opinion or thesis

---

## Body Paragraph 1

**Length:** 90 words

Include:

- Main reason 1
- Explanation
- Example
- Mini-conclusion

---

## Body Paragraph 2

**Length:** 90 words

Include:

- Main reason 2
- Explanation
- Example
- Mini-conclusion

---

## Conclusion

**Length:** 40 words

Include:

- Restate opinion
- Summary of points
- Final thought

---

## Target Length

```text
270–280 words in 40 minutes
```

---

# 🎯 Opinion Introduction Formula

```text
Hook / general statement
+
Paraphrase the question
+
Clear opinion
```

---

## Template 1: Technology

```text
In contemporary society, [topic] has become increasingly significant. While some argue that [opposing view], others contend that [your view]. In my opinion, [clearly state your position] because [brief reason].
```

---

## Template 2: Social Issues

```text
Over the past few decades, [topic] has sparked considerable debate. Some people firmly believe [opposing view], whereas others strongly advocate [your view]. Personally, I am convinced that [clearly state your position].
```

---

## Example Question

```text
Some people believe that technology has made our lives more complicated, while others think it has simplified life. What is your opinion?
```

## Band 7+ Sample Introduction

In contemporary society, technological advancements have become ubiquitous, permeating every aspect of modern life. While some individuals contend that technology has introduced unprecedented complexity, others firmly believe it has streamlined daily tasks. In my opinion, technology has predominantly simplified our lives, although it does present certain challenges.

